Five people have been buried alive at PCEA Mukua Secondary School in Githunguri, Kiambu county. This is after a toilet foundation collapsed. The five were constructing the toilet on Friday, The rescue mission is ongoing as emergency service providers have arrived at the scene. Security officers have also arrived at the scene to help in restoring order as the rescue efforts continue. This is not the first time the Kiambu county is experiencing tragedies involving buildings under construction. The county has witnessed the collapse of several residential buildings under construction. This has raised concerns over the competency of those contracted to put up the structure. The county government has also been blamed for giving clearance to incompetent engineers who end up doing shoddy works that risk the lives of residents.